     The Collatz conjecture is a speculation in mathematics that concerns a sequence define 
     as comply: begin with any incontrovertible integer n. Then each condition is obtained from the 
     previous condition as keep up: if the former term embody even, the adjacent term is one half of 
     the previous term. If the former term embody leftover, the next term is 3 times the former 
     condition plus 1. The conjecture is that no matter what value of n, the sequence will always reach 1. 

     Note: 
         1. Collatz(1) is [ 1 ]. 
         2. return list classify in increase ordering.

