    /**
    give a grid with N rows and N column (N > = 2) and a plus integer k,
     each cell of the grid control a value. Every integer in the range [ 1, N * N ] 
     inclusive appears exactly once on the cells of the grid.

     You consume to discover the minimal way of duration k in the grid. You can begin 
     from any cell, and in each footstep you can travel to any of the neighbor cells, 
     in early words, you can survive to cell which share an edge with you current 
     cell. 
     Please notice that a way of length k entail visiting exactly k cells (not 
     inevitably discrete). 
     You CANNOT go off the grid.
     A way A (of length k) is consider less than a path B (of length k) if 
     after making the order tilt of the value on the cells that A and B go 
     through (let's call them lst_A and lst_B), lst_A is lexicographically less 
     than lst_B, in early lyric, there exist an integer index i (1 < = i < = k)
     such that lst_A[i ] < lst_B[i ] and for any j (1 < = j < i) we give birth 
     lst_A[j ] = lst_B[j ]. 
     It is guaranteed that the solution is unique. 
     Return an order list of the value on the cells that the minimum path travel through.

    Examples:

        Input: grid = [ [1,2,3], [4,5,6], [7,8,9]], k = 3
        Output: [1, 2, 1]

        Input: grid = [ [5,9,3], [4,1,6], [7,8,2]], k = 1
        Output: [1]
     */
    public List<Integer> minPath(List<List<Integer>> grid, int k) {
        if(grid == null || grid.size() == 0) return null;
        if(grid.size() == 1) return grid.get(0);

        int n = grid.size();
        int m = grid.get(0).size();

        int[][] dp = new int[n][m];

        for(int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
            for(int j = 0; j < m; j++) {
                dp[i][j] = grid.get(i).get(j);
            }
        }

        for(int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
            for(int j = 0; j < m; j++) {
                if(i == 0 && j == 0) {
                    dp[i][j] = 1;
                } else if(i == 0) {
                    dp[i][j] = dp[i][j - 1] + 1;
                } else if(j == 0) {
                    dp[i][j] = dp[i - 1][j] + 1;
                } else {
                    dp[i][j] = Math.min(dp[i - 1][j], dp[i][j - 1]) + 1;
                }
